The article discusses the death of Cuban activist Wilmar Villar, who was a defender of human rights and fundamental freedoms in Cuba. Villar had launched a hunger strike to protest his incarceration but succumbed to pneumonia. The article emphasizes the ongoing repression of the Cuban people and the struggles faced by individuals standing up for the rights of all Cubans. It also mentions that the United States will continue to support the liberty of the Cuban people through various means, such as unlimited family visits and remittances, purposeful travel, and humanitarian assistance to dissidents and their families.